window.bookSummaryJSON = "<p><b>The second book in the bestselling Goodreads Choice Award–nominated series about a woman kept within the walls of a terrifying dystopian prison, where her survival means fighting back against the very men who have been raised to subjugate her.</b><br> <br> The second book in the dark, twisted, and riveting 24690 series from internationally bestselling author A.A. Dark.<br> <br> Bram Whitlock, a successful, wealthy attorney, secretly rules an underground, hidden community called Whitlock where men are masters and women are their slaves. Everleigh is a headstrong young slave in the Whitlock community who has refused to abide by the draconian rules set forth. But when Everliegh’s master is killed, she must be auctioned off to a new master. Bram Whitlock is deeply in love with Everleigh but knows keeping her will only lead to disaster. But when he finds a solution to the problem in another master, they are all fully prepared for the hell they are about to unleash.<br> <br> A dark, unpredictable portrait of psychological terror with twists and turns that make it impossible to guess where the story is going.</p>"; 
